    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-05-11T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-05-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="1105"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1105">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.11/4229.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Consul <persName type="from">Miller</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Tampico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-05-11">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 11, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Following advice of Admiral Mayo based on instructions from Navy Department Vice
                    Consul Bevan and myself came aboard <hi rend="italic">Connecticut</hi>
                    yesterday. About twenty Americans remained ashore refusing to leave Tampico.
                    German Consul is looking after Americans during my temporary absence from
                    shore.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Miller</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
